Target System              — Attack surface
 ├─ Network Exposure       — Reachability
 │   ├─ IP Address         — Discovery target
 │   ├─ Open Port          — Entry point
 │   │   ├─ Service        — Running daemon
 │   │   └─ Protocol       — TCP / UDP
 │   │
 │   └─ Firewall Rules     — Filtering
 │
 ├─ Application Layer      — Primary attack vector
 │   ├─ Protocol           — HTTP / HTTPS / SSH / FTP
 │   ├─ REST API           — Endpoint surface
 │   │   ├─ Endpoint       — URL path
 │   │   ├─ Method         — GET / POST / PUT / DELETE
 │   │   ├─ Parameters     — User input
 │   │   └─ Payload        — JSON / Form data
 │   │
 │   ├─ Auth Mechanism     — Tokens / Sessions / Keys
 │   └─ Input Handling     — Validation
 │
 ├─ Transport Layer        — Session control
 │   ├─ TCP Connection     — State tracking
 │   ├─ TLS               — Encryption boundary
 │   └─ Timing             — Side channels
 │
 ├─ Process Space          — Execution context
 │   ├─ Service Process    — Target PID
 │   ├─ Threads            — Concurrency model
 │   ├─ Memory             — Heap / Stack
 │   └─ File Descriptors   — Sockets / Files
 │
 ├─ OS Layer               — Privilege boundary
 │   ├─ User               — Permission level
 │   ├─ Capabilities       — Partial privileges
 │   ├─ Syscalls           — Kernel interface
 │   └─ Sandbox            — Containment
 │
 ├─ Kernel                 — Trust boundary
 │   ├─ Sockets            — Network objects
 │   ├─ Buffers            — Data handling
 │   ├─ Scheduler          — CPU time
 │   └─ Drivers            — Hardware interface
 │
 └─ Hardware               — Physical limits
     ├─ CPU                — Side-channel target
     ├─ Memory             — Row / cache attacks
     └─ NIC                — Packet injection / sniffing

IP → Port → Service → Protocol → API Endpoint → Input → Process → Memory → Privilege → Kernel → Hardware
